DESCRIPTION: Medical claim number. It is unique identifier for a claim, and it generally applied from Claim Header Num, Claim Line Num, etc.
Description of claim type i.e. Medical (MED), Dental (DEN), Vision (VIS), Rx-Medical (RX-MED) etc.

HI=Hospital Inpatient,
HO=Hospital Outpatient
PB=Professional
LB=Lab
Relationship flag to identify member as Enrollee(E), Spouse(S) or Dependent(D)
Date of service starts (Admission date for admissions)
Date of service ends (Discharge date for admissions)
Bill type codes to store claims as Facility(F), Ancillary(A) and Professional(P).
Diagnosis or International Classification of Diseases (ICD-9) code
Procedure code type such as 'CPT', 'HCPCS', 'REV', 'ICDOPROC', 'DRG' etc.
Primary procedure code could be any CPT, HCPCS, ICDOPROC, REV or DRG.

Diagnosis-related group (DRG) codes Indicates the diagnostic related group to which a hospital claim belongs for prospective payment purposes. For CMS data, map it from DGNS_DRG_CD field of Part A Claims Header File
Healthcare Common Procedure Coding System (HCPCS) code
Category II CPT codes are used to measure performance which is added for HEDIS purpose

Type of DRG:
APDRG: All Patient - Diagnosis Relared Group (Leading 'A')
DRG: Diagnosis Related Group (Leading 'D')
MSDRG: Medicare Severity - Diagnosis Related Group (Leading 'M')
Patient Discharge Status (2 digit long UB04/CMS codes)

Type of Bill (TOB) Information (UB04/CMS), three characters long
- First digit (character) as 'Type of facility',
- Second digit (character) as 'Bill Classification'
- Third digit (character) as 'Frequency'. 
Example - 110 (Hospital, Inpatient Non Payment/ Zero claim)
Provider identification number such as client specific number or NPI
First name of provider, if applicable
Last name of provider, if applicable
Higher level of provider specialty code, if required
Higher level of provider specialty description, if required

Number of units:
For CMS client, map it from following fields in different files:
Part A Revenue file: CLM_LINE_SRVC_UNIT_QTY
Part B Physician file: CLM_LINE_SRVC_UNIT_QTY
Amount of savings as generated by PPO network
Lab test reading best on procedure
Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) code of industry
Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) description of industry

Type of ICD (ICD9/ICD10)
Note: Default 'ICD9'. For claims incurred before 2015-10-15, it should be 'ICD9'. Otherwise, it should be 'ICD10'
Header of the Claim Number. This is the Claim Number field obtained from Client

Medicare Claim Type Code. This is the code used to identify the type of claims record being processed in NCH (National Claims History) which is consumed by CMS. 
Possible codes for this field are: 
10 (HHA CLAIM), 
20 (SNF NON-SWING BED CLAIM), 
30 (SNF SWING BED CLAIM), 
40 (HOSPITAL OUTPATIENT CLAIM), 
41 (OUTPATIENT FULL ENCOUNTER CLAIM), 
42 (OUTPATIENT ABBREVIATED ENCOUNTER CLAIM), 
50 (HOSPICE CLAIM), 
60 (INPATIENT CLAIM), 
61 (INPATIENT FULL ENCOUNTER CLAIM), 
62 (INPATIENT ABBREVIATED ENCOUNTER CLAIM), 
71 (RIC O non-DMEPOS CLAIM), 
72 (RIC O DMEPOS CLAIM), 
73 (PHYSICIAN ENCOUNTER CLAIM), 
81 (RIC M non-DMEPOS DMERC CLAIM), 
82 (RIC M DMEPOS DMERC CLAIM). 
Map it from CLM_TYPE_CD field of Part A Claims Header File.
Source: https://resdac.org/cms-data/variables/nch-claim-type-code

Indicates the type and priority of inpatient services: 
Claim Admission Type Codes are:
1=Emergency, 
2=Urgent, 
3=Elective, 
4=Newborn, 
5=Trauma Center, 
6=Reserved, 
9=Unknown

Claim Admission Source Code Indicates the source of the beneficiary's referral for admission or visit (e.g., a physician or another facility) Find Admission Source Codes here: www.resdac.org/cms-data/variables/Claim-Source-Inpatient-Admission-Code 
For CMS data, map it from CLM_ADMSN_SRC_CD field of Part A Claims Header File.

Claim Medicare Non-Payment Reason Code Indicates the reason payment on an institutional claim is denied Find Medicare Non-Payment Reason Codes here: www.resdac.org/cms-data/variables/claim-medicare-non-payment-reason-code 
For CMS data, map it from CLM_MDCR_NPMT_RSN_CD field of Part A Claims Header file

CMS Certification Number for a facility provider.
A facility's Medicare Medicaid identification number. 
It is also known as a Medicare Medicaid Provider Number, or CCN.
This number verifies that a provider has been Medicare certified for a particular type of service. 
Map it from PRVDR_OSCAR_NUM field of Part A Claims Header File.

Claim Adjustment Type Code 
Indicates whether the claim is an original, cancellation, or adjustment claim
Claim Adjustment Type Codes are: 
0=Original Claim 
1=Cancellation Claim 
2=Adjustment claim 

For CMS data, map it from CLM_ADJSMT_TYPE_CD field of Part A Claims Header File.

Claims Query Code 
Indicates the type of claim/record being processed with respect to payment 
(e.g., debit/credit indicator or interim/final indicator). 
Claim Query Codes are: 
0=Credit adjustment, 
1=Interim bill, 
2=HHA benefits exhausted, 
3=Final bill
4=Discharge notice
5=Debit adjustment
For CMS data, map it from CLM_QUERY_CD field of Part A Claims Header file

Principal Diagnosis Code for admissions 
The International Classification of Diseases (ICD)-9/10 diagnosis code identifies the beneficiary's 
principal illness or disability 
For CMS data, map this from PRNCPL_DGNS_CD field of Part A Claims Header File.

Admitting Diagnosis Code for admission
The ICD-9/10 diagnosis code identifies the illness or disability for which the beneficiary was admitted
For CMS data, map this from ADMTG_DGNS_CD field of Part A Claims Header File.

Header Claim From Date
The first day on the billing statement that covers services rendered to the beneficiary
Also known as 'Statement Covers From Date'.
For CMS data, map this from CLM_FROM_DT field of Part A Claims Header File.

Header Claim Thru Date
The last day on the billing statement that covers services rendered to the beneficiary.
Also known as 'Statement Covers Through Date'.
For CMS data, map this from CLM_THRU_DT field of Part A Claims Header File.

Claim Outpatient Service Type Code. 
Indicates the type and priority of outpatient service. 
Claim Outpatient Service Type Codes are: 
0 = Blank, 
1 = Emergency, 
2 = Urgent, 
3 = Elective, 
5-8 = Reserved, 
9 = Unknown. 
For CMS data, map this from CLM_OP_SRVC_TYPE_CD field of Part A Claims Header File.
Plan number for which the claim is billed
Plan name for which the claim is billed
Plan type for which the claim is billed

Valid Code to identify Population Type
CM - Commercial, MC - Medicare, MD - Medicaid

Payment Type Code for the claim. It can have following 3 letter values: 
FFS: Fee for Service, 
P4P: Pay for Performance, 
CAP: Capitation, 
BUN: Bundled Payment, 
DRG: DRG, 
OTH: Other.

POA (Present on Admission) flag for First Diagnosis Code. 
Possible values for POA Flag are: 
Y: Diagnosis was present at the time of inpatient admission, 
N: Diagnosis was not present at the time of inpatient admission, 
U: Unknown - Documentation insufficient to determine if condition was present at the time of inpatient admission, 
W: Clinically undetermined. Provider unable to clinically determine whether the condition was present at the time of inpatient admission, 
1: Not provided from data vendor

Note: Default '1'.
Contains the positive or negative indicator for diabetes eye exam for CDC. Must contain a 'P' for positive or a 'N' for negative.
Facility location number. For hospitals, enter the Medicare Hospital ID in this field used for the HAI measure.
Additional CPT category II: CPT-4 procedure code

Admission codes for transfer for the AHRQ PQI Medicaid measures: - 
02 = Another hospital, 
03 = Another facility, including long-term care Point of Origin UB-04 Codes, 
04 = Transfer from a Hospital
05 = Transfer from a Skilled Nursing Facility or Intermediate Care Facility (ICF), 
06 = Transfer from another health care facility
Claim number. Required for BCBS Association retrieval clients only
